The rebel group, Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC), has killed no fewer than 46 people in a village in Ituri province, local authorities said Friday. The victims, all Pygmies, were beheaded, according to interior minister of the province, Adjio Gigi. The victims were all killed between  late Wednesday and early Thursday by the  rebels. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Only a woman with gunshot wound, and her two-year-old child, managed to escape to report the killing to the authorities. ADF rebels have since last year expanded their actions in Ituri and North-Kivu province, committing massacres against civilians. Hong Kong’s Lunar New Year Fireworks Cancelled Again Auckland City Withdraw From FIFA Club World Cup Over Home Country’s Virus Restrictions The killings have continued in spite of operations against them by government troops and the UN mission in the region. (Xinhua/NAN)